oncern with ritual, and unbending demands for total commitment. These movements, however they pursue world transformation and personal transcendence, are a prominent and continuing aspect of our present condition. This book is a strong reminder that, no matter what the cause, revolution is not a thing of the past and the fervent search for another world continues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAnti-globalization movement. 0aMillennialismxPolitical aspects. 0aSocial movements. 0aWorld politicsx21st century. 0aWorld politicsy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh1 aZúquete, José Pedro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477422240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804774222423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804774222.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles